TopicTitle: Unable to click things in the main startup menu

Articles.Content:
Hello Everyone,

I've recently encountered a glitch where i cannot click anything in the start menu. When i click them they change to a whiteish colour.  In the debug menu i have a error code. Also this is my mod list. I've looked at posts on the forums and reddit threads about this glitch and i've tried everything and nothing is working. Could someone please help?
I’m going to guess one of your visual mods is out of date. If you check inside your KSP log (main KSP folder) and find the error it’ll ID which one is the culprit.

5 minutes ago, FruitGoose said:

I’m going to guess one of your visual mods is out of date. If you check inside your KSP log (main KSP folder) and find the error it’ll ID which one is the culprit.

It's still not working, i tried removing all of my graphics mod and it still didn't work...

Is there anything else i could provide or any other ideas you could give me to fix it?

3 hours ago, Plagate said:

It's still not working, i tried removing all of my graphics mod and it still didn't work...

Is there anything else i could provide or any other ideas you could give me to fix it?

Just the log. You’ll need to add it to somewhere like Dropbox and put the link here as you can’t post stuff directly. It’s in main KSP folder (ie one with GameData in) called KSPLog or something similar (basically a text file). There is another log which is more detailed if that doesn’t provide the answer.
